<item>
            <title>[LU-17539] replay-single-lmv test_1a, test_1b, test_2a failures</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17539</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It appears that the infrequently-run &lt;tt&gt;replay-single-lmv.sh&lt;/tt&gt; test script has grown some failures since it was last (ever?) run.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;it does not call &lt;tt&gt;exit_status&lt;/tt&gt; at the end of the script, so any subtest failures are not reported to the test runner&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;test_1a, test_1b, test_2a, and sometimes test_3a fail. This very likely due to outdated assumptions that &quot;&lt;tt&gt;mkdir $DIR/dir01&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; will create &lt;tt&gt;dir01&lt;/tt&gt; on MDT0000.  However, that hasn&apos;t been true since &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14792&quot; title=&quot;DNE3: enable filesystem-wide default LMV&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-14792&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-14792&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; llite: enable filesystem-wide default LMV&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; was landed.  Those assumptions were mostly fixed by &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14909&quot; title=&quot;LU-13417 patch breaks few recovery tests&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-14909&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-14909&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; test: mkdir_on_mdt0 to mkdir on MDT0&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; for other similar tests, but &lt;tt&gt;replay-single-lmv.sh&lt;/tt&gt; is not run by default.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
